<item>
            <title>[LU-12533] Improve readahead RPC issuance for large window sizes</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-12533</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Currently, when the Lustre readahead window crosses a stripe boundary, the lov_io_submit code stops there and sends an RPC.&#160; This means that for striped files &amp;amp; large readahead windows, we will send RPCs sized, at maximum, stripe_size.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This is unnecessary - If a readahead window hits the same stripe more than once, we can take advantage of that fact and submit larger RPCs.&#160; This is particularly apparent in strided readahead.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
